cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper is about pretraining a document model for text classification, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses a variational autoencoder, which is a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves semi-supervised learning, which is a common theme in both cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is a subfield of information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
